      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"taking one step at a time\" sounds like something from a textbook but it just doesn't work in real life. there is no \"next step\" when you owe millions. every time i close my eyes i just see the numbers and the look on my co-founders faces. it's not just a bad phase, it's a permanent disaster. i feel like i've already died, i'm just walking around as a ghost. everything is just... finite. there's an end to the options.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
